snippet: A grand jury that has heard evidence of ticket-fixing by police union officials finished most of its work Friday, after voting to charge as many as 17 police officers and 5 other people with a range of crimes.
lead_paragraph: A grand jury that has heard evidence of ticket-fixing by police union officials finished most of its work Friday, after voting to charge as many as 17 police officers and 5 other people with a range of crimes.
